data.title: amazing if your sick
data.body:
Kleenex tissues have been a consistent companion in my daily life, offering reliability and comfort. The softness of the tissues provides a gentle touch during moments of need, whether it's for wiping away tears, tackling a runny nose, or simply maintaining cleanliness. The brand's commitment to quality is evident in the durability of the tissues, preventing them from easily tearing or shredding.

What sets Kleenex apart is the variety of options they offer, from ultra-soft tissues to those infused with soothing ingredients like aloe and vitamin E. The convenient packaging ensures that a tissue is always within arm's reach, be it in a tissue box, a pocket-sized pack, or a stylish tissue holder. The versatility of Kleenex tissues extends beyond personal use, making them a practical solution for everyday spills or unexpected messes.

Kleenex's long-standing reputation for excellence, combined with their commitment to sustainability, adds an extra layer of assurance for conscientious consumers. Overall, Kleenex tissues consistently deliver on their promise of softness, strength, and convenience, making them a household essential for both practical and comforting purposes.

data.title: Better value than the Stop n Shop brand
data.body:
I started looking elsewhere for certain household products based partly on necessity, but also out of resentment for Stop n Shop's greediness.

I always bought the Stop n Shop brand tissue for like $1.09 a box because the name brand was $2.49 a box. However, they used the pandemic related inflation to exorbitantly jack up prices on a lot of products. Now the Stop n Shop brand is $2.39 a box, so they're pricing it slightly cheaper, but still squeezing us for as much as they can.

I understand small increases related to inflation, but this is one example (of many) where it's ridiculous greed.

My only issue with Kleenex brand is they have to be fully submersed to be flushed, so throwing a tissue in the toilet with an immediate flush usually means it ain't going down. ðŸ¤£
